Installation directions for libcommon
-------------------------------------

Prerequisites:
  blitz++ (http://www.oonumerics.org/blitz/)
  GSL     (http://sources.redhat.com/gsl/)
  HDF5    (http://hdf.ncsa.uiuc.edu/HDF5/)
  XML2    (http://dan.egnor.name/xml2/)
  SPRNG2  (http://pathintegrals.info/sprng2)
  LAPACK  (http://www.netlib.org/lapack/)
  BLAS    (http://www.netlib.org/blas/)
  CBLAS   (http://www.intel.com/software/products/mkl/docs/mklqref/cblas.htm)
  FFTW3   (http://www.fftw.org/)
  MPI     (http://www.lam-mpi.org/, http://www-unix.mcs.anl.gov/mpi/mpich/)

Quick setup
-----------

  - Unpack:
      tar xvzpf libcommon-x.x.tar.gz
  - configure:
      cd libcommon-x.x
      ./configure --prefix=/usr --enable-mpi --with-mpi-libs="..." 
    Here, the ... are the linker commands necessary to link in the
    mpi libraries.  For example, these can be found when using LAM/MPI
    by doing "mpic++ --showme" and copying everything after the "g++".

  - Compile:
    If everything when well with configure, do
       make

  - Install:
    If everything compiled, all that's left to do is
       make install


